<TITLE> AL finalises manifesto </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 6 (bdnews24.com)  Awami League has finalised its manifesto with pledges said to include battling inflation and slashing the prices of essentials, continuing the drive against corruption, thwarting Islamic militants and safeguarding the secularity of the nation. The final work was concluded at a three-hour central working committee meeting on Saturday, ending shortly before 2pm, at the party president's Dhanmondi officethough no formal briefing was given afterwards. Emerging from the meeting, AL presidium member Amir Hossain Amu informed reporters only that the final election manifesto had been approved. However, fellow presidium member Sheikh Fazlul Karim Selim mentioned promises to cut prices of commodities, drives against corruption and militants and safeguarding "the secularity of the nation". Party chief Sheikh Hasina will formally roll out the manifesto at the Hotel Sheraton on Dec. 12, AL spokesman and general secretary Syed Ashraful Islam told reporters the previous day. bdnews
